 The funeral industry's Unification Task Team has been threatening a nationwide strike over death certificates. eNCA’s senior reporter Aviwe Mtila filed this report. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Home Affairs has been granted an interdict that prohibits undertakers from intimidating its staff. On Tuesday, police clashed with protesters when they tried to shut down the Home Affairs head office in Pretoria. READ: Undertakers protest turns violent The funeral industry's Unification Task Team has been threatening a nationwide strike over death certificates. It says it will seek legal action before it makes a decision but is adamant it’s not backing down. Watch the video above for more on this story.